{"type":"message","id":"c6cf1743","parentId":"6e8a2daa","timestamp":"2026-02-15T08:52:17.705Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Audit of `C:\\Users\\west2\\.openclaw` complete. Here are the findings based on your steps:\n\n### 1. File Structure Mapping\nThe directory structure is clean and follows the standard OpenClaw layout.\n- **Core Configs:** Located in the root (`openclaw.json`, `ARKADY_CORE.md`).\n- **Internal Data:** Managed in subdirectories like `browser`, `canvas`, `cron`, `identity`, `logs`, `media`, and `memory`.\n- **Agents:** Two locations found. `C:\\Users\\west2\\.openclaw\\agents\\main` (likely binary/system) and the project-specific definitions in `C:\\Users\\west2\\.openclaw\\workspace\\.openclaw\\agents`.\n\n### 2. Auth Profiles & Anthropic/Claude Keys\n- **`auth-profiles.json`:** Does not exist in the root `.openclaw` directory.\n- **Anthropic/Claude Check:** Inspected `openclaw.json` and agent definitions in the workspace. No legacy Anthropic (`claude`, `sonnet`, `2.5`) keys or model strings were found. The system is fully transitioned to the Vertex AI stack (`google-vertex/gemini-3-pro-preview`).\n\n### 3. Subdirectories (Agents & Plugins)\n- **Agents:** All 13 SACS-2026 fleet agents (QUANT, NET, SENTINEL, OPS, DB, LOG, DMARKET, WAXPEER, STEAM, HYPE, INVENTORY, SEC, ENGINE) are present in the workspace agents folder.\n- **Plugins:** No `plugins` folder exists in the root `.openclaw` directory. Plugins are currently managed via the `openclaw.json` configuration (e.g., `telegram`).\n- **Skills:** Found 7 active skills in the workspace: `agent-development`, `database`, `file-organizer`, `mcporter`, `neural-memory`, `openclaw-github-assistant`, and `sw-data-visualizer`.\n\n### 4. Legacy Keys Review (`openclaw.json`)\n- **Findings:** `openclaw.json` is clean. It correctly points to the Vertex AI environment (`arkady-bot-dev`) and uses `gemini-3-pro-preview` as the primary model.\n- **Legacy Artifacts:** There are several backups (`openclaw.json.bak.1` through `.4`) which may contain old keys. These are inactive but could be purged if they pose a security risk.\n\n### Summary of Audit:\n- **Anthropic/Claude Keys:** **NONE FOUND**. The transition to Vertex AI is complete.\n- **Old Folders/Plugins:** No redundant plugins found. The `agents` folder in the workspace is the source of truth for the Vertex stack.\n- **Anomalies:** No major anomalies. The presence of two `agents` directories (one in root, one in workspace) is typical for OpenClaw when separating system defaults from user-defined agents.\n\nThe environment is healthy and aligned with the **SACS-2026 Vertex AI** requirements.","textSignature":"CiEBjz1rXydQ6a/UhObEU8rpKwqFBeFElaIpjH5YI89Cq8o="}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":83413,"output":668,"cacheRead":79488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84081,"cost":{"input":0.0417065,"output":0.002004,"cacheRead":0.0039744,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0476849}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771145532526}}
